<item>
            <title>[SPARK-34681] Full outer shuffled hash join when building left side produces wrong result</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-34681</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For full outer shuffled hash join with building hash map on left side, and having non-equal condition, the join can produce wrong result.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The root cause is `boundCondition` in `HashJoin.scala` always assumes the left side row is `streamedPlan` and right side row is `buildPlan` (streamedPlan.output ++ buildPlan.output). This is valid assumption, except for full outer + build left case.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix is to correct `boundCondition` in `HashJoin.scala` to handle full outer + build left case properly. See reproduce in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-32399?focusedCommentId=17298414&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels%3Acomment-tabpanel#comment-17298414&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-32399?focusedCommentId=17298414&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels%3Acomment-tabpanel#comment-17298414&lt;/a&gt;&#160;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
